<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="39" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,575,1082]" pageId="12" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,575,601]" pageId="12" pageNumber="39">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Length of male 
<quantity box="[474,568,576,602]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" pageId="12" pageNumber="39" unit="mm" value="3.1">3.1 mm</quantity>
. Ground color stramineous, infused with brown; anteclypeus, lateral margin of frontoclypeus, mesonotal triangles, mesosternum, and abdominal terga brown; forewing without distinct markings. Male pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[510,603,656,682]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="14.[151,255,1563,1587]" captionTargetBox="[278,1261,789,1525]" captionTargetId="figure-314@14.[275,1312,789,1539]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 4. New South American spp. of Neozygina, male pygofer (A, D, G, N), aedeagus in lateral (B, E, H, J, L, O) and posterior (C, F, I, K, M, P) views. A–C, N. abancayensis; D–F, N. argentiniensis; G–I, N. asymmetrica; J–K, N. expanda; L–M, N. forcipata; N–P, N. retrorsa." pageId="12" pageNumber="39">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
) with dorsal appendage arising near base, slender, acuminate, elevated and slightly arched above margin, in dorsal view curved slightly laterad, extended to apex of pygofer; ventral appendage arising preapically, well developed, extended dorsomesad. Aedeagus (figs. 4B, C) with preatrium short; shaft slightly compressed, in lateral view sinuate, with pair of subbasal dorsal teeth; paired subbasal processes approximately half length of shaft, divergent from shaft in lateral view, divergent from each other in posterior view at ca. 45° angle; paired distal processes arising near apex, moderately long, slender, extended ventrolaterad; gonopore apical.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
